[info] Activation of plug-in SEC Inline Transforms successful, version 19.2. - transforms/SEC

[DQC.US.0167.10101] In the statement 00000003 - Statement - Condensed Consolidated Statements of Operations and Comprehensive Income/(Loss) the filer has defined multiple roots calculation elements that do not have a valid calculation tree defined. The root element NetIncomeLoss has sibling root elements of us-gaap:IncomeLossFromContinuingOperationsBeforeIncomeTaxesExtraordinaryItemsNoncontrollingInterest in the filing. The sibling element us-gaap:IncomeLossFromContinuingOperationsBeforeIncomeTaxesExtraordinaryItemsNoncontrollingInterest should appear as a calculation descendant of NetIncomeLoss. This sibling element(s) are defined as calculation descendants in the US GAAP taxonomy.
